tool.name: XTandemAdapter
tool.description: Annotates MS/MS spectra using X! Tandem.
tool.command:
XTandemAdapter -xtandem_executable xtandem
#if $param_in: -in $param_in #end if #if $param_out: -out $param_out #end if #if $param_database: -database $param_database #end if #if $param_default_config_file: -default_config_file $param_default_config_file #end if #if $param_ignore_adapter_param: -ignore_adapter_param #end if #if $param_precursor_mass_tolerance: -precursor_mass_tolerance $param_precursor_mass_tolerance #end if #if $param_fragment_mass_tolerance: -fragment_mass_tolerance $param_fragment_mass_tolerance #end if #if $param_precursor_error_units: -precursor_error_units $param_precursor_error_units #end if #if $param_fragment_error_units: -fragment_error_units $param_fragment_error_units #end if #if $param_min_precursor_charge: -min_precursor_charge $param_min_precursor_charge #end if #if $param_max_precursor_charge: -max_precursor_charge $param_max_precursor_charge #end if #if $param_allow_isotope_error: -allow_isotope_error $param_allow_isotope_error #end if
#if $rep_param_fixed_modifications: -fixed_modifications #for token in $rep_param_fixed_modifications: #if " " in str(token): "$token.param_fixed_modifications" #else $token.param_fixed_modifications #end if #end for #end if
#if $rep_param_variable_modifications: -variable_modifications #for token in $rep_param_variable_modifications: #if " " in str(token): "$token.param_variable_modifications" #else $token.param_variable_modifications #end if #end for #end if #if $param_missed_cleavages: -missed_cleavages $param_missed_cleavages #end if #if $param_minimum_fragment_mz: -minimum_fragment_mz $param_minimum_fragment_mz #end if #if $param_cleavage_site: -cleavage_site $param_cleavage_site #end if #if $param_output_results: -output_results $param_output_results #end if #if $param_max_valid_expect: -max_valid_expect $param_max_valid_expect #end if #if $param_refinement: -refinement #end if #if $param_use_noise_suppression: -use_noise_suppression #end if #if $param_semi_cleavage: -semi_cleavage #end if #if $adv_opts.adv_opts_selector=='advanced': #if $adv_opts.param_force: -force #end if #end if

param.name: param_database
param.label: FASTA file or pro file
param.help: (-database) Non-existing relative file-names are looked up via'OpenMS.ini:id_db_dir'

param.name: param_default_config_file
param.label: Default parameters input file, defaulting to the ones in the OpenMS/share folder.All parameters of this adapter take precedence over this file! Use it for parameters not available here!

param.name: param_ignore_adapter_param
param.label: The config given in 'default_config_file' is used exclusively! No matter what other parameters (apart from -in,-out,-database,-xtandem_executable) are saying

param.name: param_allow_isotope_error
param.label: If set, misassignment to the first and second isotopic 13C peak are also considered

param.name: param_fixed_modifications
param.label: Fixed modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms,

param.name: param_variable_modifications
param.label: Variable modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms,

param.name: param_missed_cleavages
param.label: Number of possible cleavage sites missed by the enzyme

param.name: param_cleavage_site
param.label: The enzyme used for peptide digestion

param.name: param_output_results
param.label: Which hits should be reported
param.help: (-output_results) All, valid ones (passing the E-Value threshold), or stochastic (failing the threshold)

param.name: param_max_valid_expect
param.label: Maximal E-Value of a hit to be reported (only evaluated if 'output_result' is 'valid' or 'stochastic'

param.name: param_refinement
param.label: Enable the refinement
param.help: (-refinement) For most applications (especially when using FDR, PEP approaches) it is NOT recommended to set this flag

param.name: param_use_noise_suppression
param.label: Enable the use of the noise suppression routines

param.name: param_semi_cleavage
param.label: If set, both termini must NOT follow the cutting rule
param.help: (-semi_cleavage) For most applications it is NOT recommended to set this flag

tool.help:
Annotates MS/MS spectra using X! Tandem.
For more information, visit http://ftp.mi.fu-berlin.de/OpenMS/release-documentation/html/TOPP_XTandemAdapter.html
